<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1596,2089]" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">
The chromosome number of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hoffmann" authorityYear="1900" box="[537,697,1596,1621]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphagneticola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[537,697,1596,1621]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Sphagneticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
× 
<emphasis box="[738,920,1596,1621]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">guangdongensis</emphasis>
was 2 
<emphasis box="[1003,1017,1596,1621]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">n</emphasis>
= 53 (
<figureCitation box="[1107,1202,1596,1621]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1075,1096]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,190,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-14@3.[170,1417,190,1050]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mitotic metaphase chromosomes (A) and karyotype (B) of Sphagneticola × guangdongensis, both same scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4784332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4784332/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). The karyotype was formulated as 2 
<emphasis box="[310,324,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">n</emphasis>
= 53 = 21sm + 
<quantity box="[502,552,1632,1657]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" unit="m" value="30.0">30m</quantity>
+ 2st (
<figureCitation box="[630,718,1632,1657]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1075,1096]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,190,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-14@3.[170,1417,190,1050]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Mitotic metaphase chromosomes (A) and karyotype (B) of Sphagneticola × guangdongensis, both same scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4784332" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4784332/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
